{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"25adee7a-6f70-450a-aafe-70cea4eec04b","content":"The `--report-trx` flag needs to be passed through to the testing platform via `--`. Let me fix the command:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Ss3Ybx9c1grVDvrZ6odRvp","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-3482d973a76044629da1689359854228 && dotnet test -- --report-trx 2>&1","description":"Run tests with TRX via platform args","initial_wait":60},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Run tests with TRX via platform args"}],"interactionId":"1a4df2f4-e779-4bc4-bff0-586a94b73b34","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The `--report-trx` flag isn't being handled correctly by `dotnet test` when `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is true. The issue is that `dotnet test` is passing `--report-trx` directly to MSBuild rather than forwarding it to the test platform.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true`, the way to pass platform-specific arguments through `dotnet test` is using `--` separator:\n\n```\ndotnet test -- --report-trx\n```\n\nLet me try that.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"4821:25E777:3133F63:35ED366:69FBE6A8"},"id":"22443a04-52d6-46cb-a188-16950bf18e9a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:11:23.634Z","parentId":"991c8d39-574d-48d6-bb0a-349162889c06"}
